                                                                                                               Hotel Leela splits with Goa partner
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, Feb. 27: Hotel Leelaventure today said it had come to a mutually amicable separation agreement with General Hotel Management, the company that has been operating and managing The Leela Goa, since April 2003.        
	From next month, Hotel Leelaventure will run the Goa property under the Leela Kempinsky brand name.        
	In view of the forthcoming openings of our new properties in Gurgaon and Udaipur and further expansion plans of The Leela in the next few years, we have decided to regroup all our properties under one marketing alliance with Kempinski, said Vivek Nair, vice-chairman and managing director, Hotel Leelaventure.         
	The Leela Palaces Hotels amp; Resorts brand is supported by a marketing franchise agreement with Switzerlands Kempinski Hotels and Resorts. Hotel Leelaventure is present at Kovalam (Kerala) and in Mumbai, Bangalore and Goa.        
	It will also have hotels in Gurgaon, Udaipur, Chennai, New Delhi, Hyderabad and Pune in the future.         
	The company will have 2,750 rooms over the next three years from 1,086 rooms now.                                                                                                                                        
